Second Lady Karen Pence traveled to Pensacola to meet with military spouses and the Blue Angels team at Naval Air Station Pensacola. She received a briefing on mental health and military spouse programs at the base's Fleet and Family Support Center, which offers free classes and services to assist military families. Mrs. Pence also discussed her role with PREVENTS, emphasizing the importance of addressing mental health and providing resources to service members and their families. She visited the Blue Angels practice area and thanked them for their flyovers during the pandemic. At the Pensacola Veterans Memorial Park, Mrs. Pence delivered remarks thanking military spouses for their contributions and outlined the Trump Administration's efforts to create employment solutions for them, including increased funding for transition assistance and meetings with governors to address occupational licensing reforms.